The paper deals with providing secrecy in communication channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of structured codes is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on two-user Gaussian channels, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
